data.title: The Collected Works of John Stuart Mill, Volume XXXI - Miscellaneous Writings
data.meta_description: Vol. 31 of the 33 vol. Collected Works contains Mill’s writings on botany and reviews of medical books. It also contains his edition of Bentham’s Rationale of Judicial Evidence and his father’s Analysis of the Phenomena of the Human Mind.
